"{\"uid\": \"express.co.uk-showbiz-tv-radio-1931040-bbc-olympics-team-gb-kit-complaint\", \"text\": \"BBCviewers have taken to social media to complain aboutTeam GB's kit. EveryOlympics, different countries take the opportunity to champion national pride by enlisting a local designer to create their uniforms.  For Paris 2024, the kit was designed by Adidas and they will continue their partnership until the 2032 Olympic Games. Boasting the red, white and blue of the Union Jack, the uniform \\\"celebrates the unique aspects of Great Britain\\\".  However, not everyone is a fan. Now that the Olympic Games are officially underway in Paris, a number of viewers have had their say on the design.  One person moaned online: \\\"What is with that GB kit tho? Horrible#Olympics.\\\" A second person also chimed in: \\\"I see Team GB are going for the most boring kit design of the Olympics! Very in brand with modern Adidas. Bring back the 1988 Olympic design I say.\\\"  A third person also commented: \\\"Yeah, not super keen on the Team GB outfits for this.#Olympics#OpeningCeremony.\\\"  READ MORE:Swiatek offers excuse for Olympics loss before walking out of interview in tears    A fourth also similarly wrote: \\\"The Team GB kits this year are absolutely dreadful #OlympicGames,\\\" as a fifth said: \\\"So we have not bothered to design proper kits for the athletes to wear this time then. Slap a black (?) Union Jack on a pale blue mac.\\\"  On the other hand, one person loved the uniform and said: \\\"The Great Britain#OpeningCeremonykit is beautiful.@TeamGBif you have got any spares lying around you want to get rid of you are welcome to send me one. DM me for my address.\\\"  Do not miss:ITV News presenter quits show after 36 years as she breaks silence on exit  Do not miss:Harry angers Palace once again as furious courtiers lash out at his latest claim  Do not miss:Denise Welch 'lost acting jobs from being opinionated on Loose Women' after rows  We use your sign-up to provide content in ways you have consented to and to improve our understanding of you. This may include adverts from us and 3rd parties based on our understanding. You can unsubscribe at any time. Read ourPrivacy Policy    In other news during the Olympics, there were remarkable scenes when a sports event came to a standstill twice. The men's skiff medal race, featuring Team GB, was already underway when it was suddenly stopped by organisers.  This was because of a sudden and dramatic shift in the wind's direction. This meant a swift restart, but then organisers stopped the event again because of a lack of wind.  The race is potentially rescheduled for Friday.BBCsailing commentator Niall Myant expressed his astonishment at the development, saying: \\\"I have never seen that in a medal race at the Olympic level.  \\\"I can only imagine it's because the breeze has drifted so dramatically, the committee have decided it's unfair so they have abandoned the race. Quite the moment. That would have been a really hard decision.\\\"  SEARCH  CONNECT WITH US  TODAY'S PAPER  See today's front and back pages, download the newspaper, order back issues and use the historic Daily Express newspaper archive.  EXPRESS.CO.UK  Daily Express uses notifications to keep you updated\"}"